Environmental degradation and decay, arising from gross abuse of resources like land, soil and water have continued to pose danger and affect the economy, the Nigerian town planners have said. The National President Nigerian Institute of Town Planners (NITP), Tpl. Lekwa Ezutah, said this at the opening ceremony of a two-day summit tagged Nigeria Green Cities Summit, held in Abuja with the theme ‘Brown to Green: Enhancing Wellness and Livability’. Tpl. Ezuta said for cities to be livable and functional, they ought to have energy -efficient facilities and buildings in their design and use “because it makes economic sense.’’ OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The town planner expert who said many of Nigerian cities were rated low in greenery and environmental beautification added that the percentage of green areas or woodlands in the built-up part of major cities of Nigeria lies between 7-10% against cities abroad which have green areas between 26-32%.  ... Want strict adherence to master plan Town planners want smart cities in Nigeria Town planners honor communications outfit Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin